WEBVTT

00:10.662 --> 00:12.142
Sherry: We played by Padre's
rules because it was

00:12.403 --> 00:14.057
a safe place for our son.

00:14.188 --> 00:15.754
This doesn't feel safe.

00:15.885 --> 00:17.626
This feels like --
Sanctuary.

00:17.756 --> 00:19.454
When Finch wakes up,
we're going to take him

00:19.584 --> 00:21.891
away from this place.
Try and be a family.

00:22.022 --> 00:23.110
What's that got
to do with me?

00:23.284 --> 00:24.633
You're family.

00:24.763 --> 00:26.939
My mother is dead
because of you!

00:27.070 --> 00:28.811
You can still have
a family, Dove.

00:28.941 --> 00:30.334
Even if it's not
the one you thought.

00:30.465 --> 00:31.857
How's he doing?

00:31.988 --> 00:34.295
There's not much
I can do for him now.

00:34.425 --> 00:36.514
Maybe we're just not
meant to be together.

00:36.688 --> 00:37.602
Where would you go?

00:37.733 --> 00:38.777
Back home.

00:38.908 --> 00:40.431
I'm sorry.

00:41.432 --> 00:43.739
[Insects chirping]

00:43.869 --> 00:45.958
[Footsteps]

00:50.224 --> 00:51.790
[Thunder rumbles]

01:07.676 --> 01:08.981
[Rattling]

01:11.027 --> 01:12.463
[Door creaks]

01:12.594 --> 01:14.639
[Door closes]

01:20.645 --> 01:22.038
[Bottles clang]

01:22.169 --> 01:25.389
[Thunder rumbles]

01:25.520 --> 01:27.087
[Bottles clang]

01:49.848 --> 01:51.850
Go out there,
and you make it right.

01:53.548 --> 01:55.158
[Clears throat]

01:57.465 --> 01:59.162
[Thunder rumbles]

02:03.210 --> 02:04.602
[Sighs]

02:33.457 --> 02:35.024
[Scraping]

02:35.155 --> 02:36.547
[Footsteps]

02:36.678 --> 02:38.462
[Man grunts]

02:38.593 --> 02:46.731
♪♪

02:46.862 --> 02:55.000
♪♪

02:55.131 --> 02:56.567
[Man coughing]

02:56.698 --> 03:02.486
♪♪

03:02.617 --> 03:08.536
♪♪

03:08.666 --> 03:10.320
Don't shoot.

03:10.451 --> 03:12.104
Please.

03:17.719 --> 03:18.937
I thought
the place was empty.

03:19.068 --> 03:21.201
Well, it's not.
Do you live here?

03:21.331 --> 03:22.767
That doesn't matter.

03:24.291 --> 03:27.032
I'm Jay.

03:27.163 --> 03:29.774
Okay. Jay.

03:29.905 --> 03:31.689
You gonna walk out, or do you
want me to drag you out?

03:31.820 --> 03:33.865
P-Please.

03:33.996 --> 03:36.085
I got robbed.

03:36.216 --> 03:39.393
What they stole, I'll die
if I don't get it back.

03:39.523 --> 03:41.438
There's nothing
that valuable anymore.

03:41.569 --> 03:44.659
It is
if you're diabetic.

03:44.789 --> 03:47.009
What did you just say?

03:47.139 --> 03:49.446
Insulin.

03:49.577 --> 03:51.796
My insulin
was in my bag.

03:54.234 --> 03:55.844
You're full of shit.
I'm not.

03:55.974 --> 03:58.107
No, there's none of that
left anymore.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.717
There was in my group.

03:59.848 --> 04:02.329
Look. We had a guy
who could make it.

04:02.459 --> 04:04.331
He had me believing
in miracles.

04:04.461 --> 04:07.116
Until these guys
came through and...

04:07.247 --> 04:08.465
they killed him.

04:10.598 --> 04:11.990
They took everything.

04:12.121 --> 04:14.776
♪♪

04:14.906 --> 04:16.038
What I had in that bag

04:16.168 --> 04:18.649
is what I had
to make it through the week.

04:20.521 --> 04:22.000
[Laughs]

04:25.308 --> 04:27.179
Are you messing with me?

04:29.312 --> 04:32.184
You expect me to believe this
is some sort of coincidence?

04:32.315 --> 04:36.493
♪♪

04:36.624 --> 04:38.190
Who told you?

04:39.801 --> 04:41.237
Told me what?

04:41.368 --> 04:43.239
[Grunts]

04:43.370 --> 04:45.676
Who told you
about me?!

04:49.114 --> 04:50.551
You said there's
a week's supply left.

04:50.681 --> 04:52.335
So what happens
after that?

04:52.466 --> 04:54.990
I don't know.

04:55.120 --> 04:58.254
But even a week is a hell
of a lot better than being dead.

04:58.385 --> 04:59.603
Please.

04:59.734 --> 05:02.345
I lost everyone.

05:02.476 --> 05:05.522
And I owe it to them
to make things right.

05:05.653 --> 05:07.307
For however
much time I got.

05:07.437 --> 05:12.268
♪♪

05:12.399 --> 05:14.705
The guys
who took your insulin.

05:14.836 --> 05:16.141
You know
where they're at?

05:16.272 --> 05:17.839
Yeah.

05:17.969 --> 05:19.841
Okay.

05:19.971 --> 05:22.060
[Walkers growling]

05:31.331 --> 05:32.767
Man #1:
Where you going?

05:32.897 --> 05:34.856
Man #2: Ah.
I gotta take a leak.

05:34.986 --> 05:36.901
[Walkers growling]

05:43.908 --> 05:45.954
[Both breathing heavily]

05:46.084 --> 05:48.435
Alright. Are you telling me
the guys that --

05:48.565 --> 05:51.220
that took your medicine...

05:51.351 --> 05:52.656
are in there?

05:52.787 --> 05:54.266
Yeah.

05:57.226 --> 05:59.228
Good luck.
No! Whoa.

05:59.359 --> 06:00.751
Okay. Look.

06:02.231 --> 06:05.060
I'm gonna ask you
one more time.

06:05.190 --> 06:06.322
Who told you about me?

06:06.453 --> 06:08.106
Nobody.
Why do you think that?

06:08.237 --> 06:12.197
Because the last time I tried
to help somebody get insulin,

06:12.328 --> 06:14.548
I ended up in there.

06:14.678 --> 06:16.376
The factory?

06:19.248 --> 06:21.685
Yeah. We didn't
call it that, though.

06:21.816 --> 06:25.123
♪♪

06:25.254 --> 06:26.777
What did you call it?

06:26.908 --> 06:30.302
♪♪

06:30.433 --> 06:32.130
The Sanctuary.

06:35.569 --> 06:40.051
My life has been shit
ever since I set foot in there.

06:40.182 --> 06:43.490
So I don't know if it's you,
you know,

06:43.620 --> 06:47.798
or the universe that's
playing some sick joke on me,

06:47.929 --> 06:50.845
but I'm not going in there --
not for you, not for anyone.

06:50.975 --> 06:52.803
Look.
We're not that different.

06:52.934 --> 06:56.851
♪♪

06:56.981 --> 06:59.680
My wife.

06:59.810 --> 07:01.725
She was everything to me.

07:01.856 --> 07:06.817
♪♪

07:06.948 --> 07:10.038
They killed her.

07:10.168 --> 07:11.822
My son, too.

07:14.303 --> 07:17.915
You came back, alone.

07:18.046 --> 07:20.483
I think you lost somebody, too.
Maybe it was your wife.

07:20.614 --> 07:23.007
Maybe it was
more than her.

07:24.748 --> 07:27.534
If you don't help me,
if we don't help each other,

07:27.664 --> 07:29.710
what are we even
doing here?

07:29.840 --> 07:32.713
♪♪

07:32.843 --> 07:34.454
Ohh...

07:34.584 --> 07:43.898
♪♪

07:44.028 --> 07:47.423
Alright.

07:47.554 --> 07:49.686
I'll meet you
back at the house.

07:49.817 --> 07:52.036
Okay.
What am I looking for?

07:53.211 --> 07:55.387
[Walker growling]

07:55.518 --> 08:02.133
♪♪

08:02.264 --> 08:08.966
♪♪

08:09.097 --> 08:15.756
♪♪

08:15.886 --> 08:22.502
♪♪

08:22.632 --> 08:29.421
♪♪

08:31.902 --> 08:41.564
♪♪

08:41.695 --> 08:51.400
♪♪

08:51.531 --> 09:01.192
♪♪

09:01.323 --> 09:11.028
♪♪

09:11.159 --> 09:20.821
♪♪

09:20.951 --> 09:30.657
♪♪

09:30.787 --> 09:40.623
♪♪

10:19.444 --> 10:22.970
[Indistinct voices]

10:23.100 --> 10:26.147
[Flames crackling]

10:26.277 --> 10:27.844
[Indistinct voices]

10:27.975 --> 10:31.152
Man: Do it!
Do it, do it, do it!

10:31.282 --> 10:33.284
Negan:
Who are you, Dwight?

10:33.415 --> 10:35.373
[Gun cocks]
Man: Turn around, asshole.

10:35.504 --> 10:41.989
♪♪

10:42.119 --> 10:48.560
♪♪

10:48.691 --> 10:50.911
What do we have there?

10:51.041 --> 10:53.870
You took a man's
medicine. I'm just here to get it back for him.

10:55.393 --> 10:57.700
Somebody did a number
on <i>your</i>face.

10:57.831 --> 11:00.311
I'm gonna
walk out of here.

11:00.442 --> 11:01.965
You'll never see me again.

11:02.096 --> 11:04.968
You stole from us.

11:05.099 --> 11:07.841
Now an example
needs to be made,

11:07.971 --> 11:10.452
starting with the <i>other</i>side
of your face.

11:10.582 --> 11:11.540
[Grunts]

11:11.671 --> 11:13.368
No! No! No! No!

11:13.498 --> 11:15.413
[Screaming]

11:17.938 --> 11:20.636
[Man screaming]

11:20.767 --> 11:22.116
[Gunshot]

11:22.246 --> 11:24.118
Man: What the hell
do you think you're doing?

11:24.248 --> 11:25.902
[Man screaming]

11:27.425 --> 11:28.688
[Gunshots]

11:28.818 --> 11:30.733
We will find you!

11:33.214 --> 11:34.694
[Grunts]

11:34.824 --> 11:37.305
Jay!

11:37.435 --> 11:39.133
Jay! Where are you?! Hey!

11:39.263 --> 11:40.395
[Coughing] Hey.

11:40.525 --> 11:42.919
Hey. I got it! Jay!

11:44.616 --> 11:46.227
[Walker growling]

11:48.098 --> 11:49.186
Oh, no.

11:49.317 --> 11:51.406
[Growling]

11:58.108 --> 11:59.849
[Growling stops]

11:59.980 --> 12:01.416
[Grunts]

12:01.546 --> 12:07.291
♪♪

12:12.470 --> 12:14.951
You should have killed me
when you had the...

12:18.476 --> 12:22.350
I tried to make it right,
Daryl. I, uh...

12:22.480 --> 12:24.482
But I guess I couldn't.

12:28.704 --> 12:30.837
You should've killed me when
you had the chance, Daryl.

12:30.967 --> 12:34.057
You should've just killed me
when you had the chance!

12:34.188 --> 12:36.625
Please!

12:36.756 --> 12:39.802
Please come and do it
right now! Please!

12:49.638 --> 12:50.987
Come on!

12:56.123 --> 12:58.168
[Vehicle approaches]

13:05.262 --> 13:06.524
[Engine shuts off]

13:06.655 --> 13:11.051
♪♪

13:11.181 --> 13:12.226
Daryl.

13:12.356 --> 13:13.531
Sherry: D?

13:13.662 --> 13:15.011
What are you doing here?

13:15.142 --> 13:16.360
D...

13:18.362 --> 13:20.016
We came here
to find you.

13:20.147 --> 13:21.539
We need you!

13:21.670 --> 13:29.721
♪♪

13:29.852 --> 13:38.034
♪♪

13:40.341 --> 13:41.559
[Groans]

13:41.690 --> 13:43.039
Sherry: Sorry.

13:45.302 --> 13:47.565
[Exhales sharply]

13:49.524 --> 13:51.221
Okay.

13:53.658 --> 13:54.964
Hm.

13:55.095 --> 13:57.575
Ah. Shit.

13:57.706 --> 14:00.013
You guys need to
get out of here.

14:00.143 --> 14:03.016
What happened, D?

14:03.146 --> 14:04.800
Who did this?

14:04.931 --> 14:06.062
That guy outside?

14:06.193 --> 14:07.194
No.

14:07.324 --> 14:08.499
Then who?

14:08.630 --> 14:10.110
It doesn't matter.

14:10.240 --> 14:13.243
If they see you here with me,
they'll kill you.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.550
[Squishing]

14:15.680 --> 14:16.681
[Groans]
Oh. Stop. St--

14:16.812 --> 14:18.031
No, no. Hold still.

14:18.161 --> 14:20.772
Okay. It's almost done.
Just do it again.

14:20.903 --> 14:23.079
Pinch. Pierce.

14:23.210 --> 14:24.689
Sorry. Okay.

14:24.820 --> 14:28.432
Yeah. And then pull.

14:28.563 --> 14:31.087
Ah. Shouldn't you
be doing this?

14:34.090 --> 14:36.963
It's better this way.

14:37.093 --> 14:40.444
Look. I'm telling you.
You need to go.

14:40.575 --> 14:42.098
We're not leaving
without you.

14:42.229 --> 14:43.534
Why?

14:43.665 --> 14:46.102
There's a fight coming.

14:46.233 --> 14:48.322
Okay.
What kind of fight?

14:48.452 --> 14:51.151
One we can't win
without you.

14:51.281 --> 14:53.675
This guy Troy.

14:53.805 --> 14:55.764
He's got a score to settle
with Madison,

14:55.895 --> 14:59.115
and he plans on settling it
by taking over PADRE.

14:59.246 --> 15:01.683
Oh, it sounds like
Madison's fight to me.

15:01.813 --> 15:04.816
Yeah, well...
she made it ours.

15:04.947 --> 15:08.646
She's M.I.A. And she left
Strand in charge.

15:08.777 --> 15:10.126
Victor's still alive?

15:10.257 --> 15:12.215
A lot has happened
since you left.

15:12.346 --> 15:14.478
Dove, want to
grab the wrap?

15:14.609 --> 15:16.654
Mm-hmm.

15:16.785 --> 15:19.309
Yeah, w-what does any of this
have to do with me?

15:19.440 --> 15:21.007
I'm -- I'm just
a little confused here.

15:21.137 --> 15:23.618
You trained every kid
on the island.

15:23.748 --> 15:25.707
They'll listen to you.
They trust you.

15:25.837 --> 15:28.579
There's nothing that
I could say or -- or do

15:28.710 --> 15:32.279
that you
couldn't do better.

15:32.409 --> 15:36.631
And what -- You.
Why -- Why are you here?

15:36.761 --> 15:39.590
PADRE is the only home
I've ever known.

15:39.721 --> 15:41.592
Without it...

15:41.723 --> 15:44.030
I don't --

15:44.160 --> 15:45.683
I got nothing.

15:53.604 --> 15:55.955
Okay. Alright.
Look. Thank you.

15:56.085 --> 15:57.521
Um...

15:59.088 --> 16:03.701
Look. I cannot help
save those kids.

16:03.832 --> 16:06.704
Okay? I-I couldn't
even save my own son.

16:06.835 --> 16:08.010
That's not your fault.

16:08.141 --> 16:09.969
No, it doesn't matter
whose fault it is.

16:10.099 --> 16:13.494
Every time I try
and make something right,

16:13.624 --> 16:14.843
someone gets hurt.

16:14.974 --> 16:17.889
That's not true.
No, it is true.

16:18.020 --> 16:19.979
The guy outside,
he needed insulin.

16:20.109 --> 16:21.545
What?
Yes.

16:21.676 --> 16:22.982
Just like your sister.

16:23.112 --> 16:24.896
He asked me for help,
and I couldn't get him

16:25.027 --> 16:26.550
his insulin in time,
and he died.

16:26.681 --> 16:27.987
So look.

16:28.117 --> 16:31.599
The best thing that
you guys can do for PADRE

16:31.729 --> 16:34.558
and for those kids
is to leave me here alone.

16:34.689 --> 16:37.126
Do you think
I <i>wanted</i>to come here?

16:37.257 --> 16:38.606
I-I -- I don't know.
Why did you?

16:38.736 --> 16:40.260
You could have given
June directions.

16:40.390 --> 16:41.609
No, no.
I didn't come here for you.

16:41.739 --> 16:43.611
- Oh. Who'd you come here for?
- Our son!

16:43.741 --> 16:45.787
Finch is gone.
[Scoffs]

16:45.917 --> 16:47.745
But PADRE isn't.

16:47.876 --> 16:49.269
That place
is the reason he's dead.

16:49.399 --> 16:51.053
Why do you want
to fight for that?

16:51.184 --> 16:52.533
Because -- Because, D!

16:52.663 --> 16:54.491
Maybe something good
could come from something bad.

16:54.622 --> 16:55.797
It can't! Okay?!

16:55.927 --> 16:57.146
We have to try!

16:57.277 --> 16:58.408
Why?!

16:58.539 --> 17:02.282
Because Finch's life
needs to mean something!

17:02.412 --> 17:04.066
And helping these kids,

17:04.197 --> 17:07.156
helping make PADRE
into something better...

17:07.287 --> 17:09.419
that is how we honor him!

17:11.987 --> 17:14.729
No, I can't go back there.

17:14.859 --> 17:16.861
I'll honor him my own way.

17:16.992 --> 17:20.996
♪♪

17:21.127 --> 17:23.042
What do you think Finch
would say if he knew

17:23.172 --> 17:26.262
his father walked away from kids
who needed protection?

17:29.787 --> 17:33.400
It's not because
I don't care about them.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.141
It's because I do.

17:35.271 --> 17:40.146
♪♪

17:40.276 --> 17:43.279
[Door opens and closes]

17:45.151 --> 17:46.456
June: Hey.
It's fine.

17:46.587 --> 17:55.465
♪♪

18:05.475 --> 18:10.089
Dove.
Can you hear me?

18:10.219 --> 18:12.874
Ah. What's wrong?

18:13.004 --> 18:15.616
Dove's missing.
Has been since we woke up.

18:15.746 --> 18:17.313
Dove, where are you?

18:19.141 --> 18:21.665
Dove, please tell us
where you are.

18:23.189 --> 18:24.842
[Vehicle approaches]

18:28.716 --> 18:32.328
It's her.
She looks hurt. Shit.

18:35.549 --> 18:37.028
Dove!

18:40.641 --> 18:42.164
Oh, my God!

18:43.470 --> 18:45.036
- What happened?
- Let me see.

18:45.167 --> 18:47.169
[Weakly] No,
I don't need your help.

18:52.000 --> 18:54.089
Dwight: Shit.

18:54.220 --> 18:56.526
There's no exit wound. We got to
get this bullet out right away.

18:56.657 --> 18:58.006
Who did this?

18:58.137 --> 19:00.400
Some assholes tried
to steal the truck.

19:00.530 --> 19:03.316
Said they were looking
for someone that burned their friend.

19:04.578 --> 19:06.057
Okay. We got to
get her inside now.

19:06.188 --> 19:08.190
Sherry: Alright. Let's get her
back in the house.

19:08.321 --> 19:09.670
Your medical kit?
June: It's not enough.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.324
I need anesthetic.
We need surgical tools.

19:11.454 --> 19:13.064
We have to get the bullet out
and get it all cleaned up

19:13.195 --> 19:15.980
before she goes
into septic shock.

19:16.111 --> 19:18.592
"We"?

19:18.722 --> 19:20.942
I can't do this
on my own, Dwight.

19:21.072 --> 19:22.813
We need to
get her help now!

19:22.944 --> 19:24.467
Is there anywhere
around here?

19:24.598 --> 19:26.817
With medical supplies.
Equipment.

19:29.255 --> 19:31.822
Marty: I should have known
she was with you!

19:31.953 --> 19:39.265
♪♪

19:39.395 --> 19:46.750
♪♪

19:46.881 --> 19:49.144
I'm sorry
about the girl.

19:49.275 --> 19:53.235
But after what you did
to Phil,

19:53.366 --> 19:57.021
hell, it feels like
some beautiful karma.

19:57.152 --> 19:58.849
What the hell
is he talking about, D?

19:58.980 --> 20:02.113
You. You're the one
that burned their friend?

20:02.244 --> 20:03.680
[Grunts]

20:06.596 --> 20:09.382
She doesn't look so hot.

20:09.512 --> 20:10.992
Maybe we could help.

20:11.122 --> 20:12.863
Doubt that.
[Scoffs]

20:12.994 --> 20:16.519
Come on. You haven't
even heard me out.

20:16.650 --> 20:17.738
Okay.

20:17.868 --> 20:19.522
You know...

20:19.653 --> 20:24.005
we have some top-notch medical
supplies back at our place.

20:24.135 --> 20:26.529
Hell, of course,
you know that.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.314
You were there.

20:28.444 --> 20:29.619
Where?

20:32.796 --> 20:34.102
The Sanctuary.

20:34.233 --> 20:35.277
What?

20:40.978 --> 20:43.372
Tick-tock.
What's it gonna be?

20:43.503 --> 20:46.593
These medical supplies.
What do you want in exchange?

20:46.723 --> 20:48.725
You know, Phil...

20:48.856 --> 20:51.989
he's right where
your friend left him,

20:52.120 --> 20:54.427
and he deserves
the satisfaction

20:54.557 --> 20:57.995
of finishing
what he started.

20:58.126 --> 21:01.434
And I intend
to give it to him.

21:01.564 --> 21:04.306
So you hand
yourself over....

21:04.437 --> 21:06.526
we'll make sure
the girl gets patched up.

21:06.656 --> 21:12.183
♪♪

21:12.314 --> 21:17.928
♪♪

21:18.059 --> 21:19.408
Nice try, asshole.

21:19.539 --> 21:21.105
[Gunfire]

21:21.236 --> 21:24.457
♪♪

21:24.587 --> 21:25.806
She needs those supplies.

21:25.936 --> 21:27.329
And she's gonna get them.

21:27.460 --> 21:29.462
We're going to
the Sanctuary. Now.

21:29.592 --> 21:31.899
No, if that psycho finds
us there, he'll kill us.

21:32.029 --> 21:34.293
[Gunfire]

21:34.423 --> 21:36.817
It's 20 miles from here.
They're on foot.

21:36.947 --> 21:39.298
We'll be in and out before
they even know we're there.

21:41.648 --> 21:43.345
Dwight: This is happening
all over again.

21:43.476 --> 21:45.391
Us, a kid who needs surgery.
I mean, it never ends.

21:45.521 --> 21:47.262
What choice do we have?

21:47.393 --> 21:48.437
She's right, D.

21:48.568 --> 21:50.352
[Gunfire]

21:51.614 --> 21:54.008
[Walkers growling]

21:54.138 --> 21:55.705
We have to go -- now.

21:55.836 --> 21:59.492
♪♪

21:59.622 --> 22:00.667
Okay.

22:00.797 --> 22:02.146
[Dove groans]

22:03.278 --> 22:04.888
[Walkers growling]

22:05.019 --> 22:10.154
♪♪

22:10.285 --> 22:15.334
♪♪

22:15.464 --> 22:20.600
♪♪

22:20.730 --> 22:25.866
♪♪

22:25.996 --> 22:28.912
Dwight: [Hushed] Careful. Some
of those guys could be here.

22:29.043 --> 22:32.307
♪♪

22:32.438 --> 22:33.830
Sherry!

22:33.961 --> 22:38.835
♪♪

22:38.966 --> 22:43.884
♪♪

22:44.014 --> 22:45.451
[Dove coughing]

22:45.581 --> 22:46.974
[Gunfire]

22:47.104 --> 22:49.106
Man:
Put down your weapons!

22:50.499 --> 22:52.762
Shit. I'm out.

22:52.893 --> 22:54.764
Can't hide forever!

22:58.812 --> 23:01.118
[Walker growling]

23:04.818 --> 23:06.123
We need to move.

23:06.254 --> 23:14.784
♪♪

23:14.915 --> 23:23.489
♪♪

23:23.619 --> 23:25.273
Dwight: The rest
of the place is clear.

23:25.404 --> 23:26.883
But we got to hurry up.

23:27.014 --> 23:29.277
W-We probably have an hour
before they get here.

23:29.408 --> 23:31.192
Yeah.
We need to get started.

23:31.322 --> 23:34.238
Um, put a load of 100 milligrams
of the lidocaine

23:34.369 --> 23:35.936
into that syringe.

23:36.066 --> 23:38.373
Best we can do for her
is subcutaneous anesthetic

23:38.504 --> 23:40.375
injections
around the wound.

23:40.506 --> 23:42.246
[Dove groaning]

23:42.377 --> 23:44.161
Sherry, you okay?

23:46.512 --> 23:47.904
Sherry.
Oh.

23:48.035 --> 23:49.863
Okay? 100 milligrams
into that syringe.

23:49.993 --> 23:52.822
Dwight, grab the rubbing alcohol
and clean the wound, okay?

23:55.999 --> 23:57.653
[Dove groaning]

24:02.876 --> 24:04.486
[Inhales sharply]
Okay. Alright, alright!

24:04.617 --> 24:06.488
[Breathing heavily]

24:06.619 --> 24:10.274
That'll do. Alright.
Take the forceps.

24:12.494 --> 24:14.627
Alright. You're gonna do
20 milligrams into the tissue

24:14.757 --> 24:17.760
all around there, okay?
Deeper, the better.

24:17.891 --> 24:19.153
Alright.

24:19.283 --> 24:21.547
[Breathing sharply]

24:21.677 --> 24:23.287
June, you should
be doing this.

24:23.418 --> 24:25.028
I already told you,
I can't.

24:25.159 --> 24:27.596
It's not the train car.

24:27.727 --> 24:29.337
It's more than that.

24:29.468 --> 24:31.382
[Dove grunting]

24:34.081 --> 24:36.779
Alright. As soon as she's numb,
you can start the extraction.

24:36.910 --> 24:39.086
H-Him? No. No. No, no.
I-I don't want him --

24:39.216 --> 24:41.218
I don't want him
to remove it. Shh.

24:41.349 --> 24:42.959
No, he's not gonna remove it.
It's gonna be okay.

24:43.090 --> 24:45.005
No, no! He couldn't even
save his own son! Dove. Stop.

24:45.135 --> 24:47.181
No. No. I'm not letting him
do the same to me!

24:47.311 --> 24:49.400
No! No! No!
June: Shh.

24:51.011 --> 24:52.316
[Rumbling]
It's okay.

24:52.447 --> 24:53.492
Whoa.

24:53.622 --> 24:56.407
[Rumbling]

24:56.538 --> 24:58.148
What is that?

24:58.279 --> 25:00.499
♪♪

25:00.629 --> 25:02.718
[Walkers growling]

25:09.377 --> 25:11.292
Dwight: The gunfire
must have drawn them.

25:11.422 --> 25:14.687
Perimeter fence is broken.
T-They're piling in.

25:14.817 --> 25:16.906
♪♪

25:17.037 --> 25:18.908
- Ohh...
- This isn't gonna work.

25:19.039 --> 25:20.997
Why not?
The bullet's too close to one of her arteries.

25:21.128 --> 25:22.912
One false move,
a slip of the hand,

25:23.043 --> 25:25.436
we could do more damage taking
it out than it did going in.

25:25.567 --> 25:27.482
We have to get them
away from the wall. Yeah.

25:27.613 --> 25:29.266
This place is hanging on
by a thread.

25:29.397 --> 25:30.659
I'll go.

25:32.400 --> 25:34.271
Well, I'm coming with.
No! No, no, no.

25:34.402 --> 25:37.710
You stay with June, and I'll
hold them off as long as I can.

25:37.840 --> 25:43.890
♪♪

25:44.020 --> 25:45.587
[Walkers growling]

25:47.807 --> 25:49.852
[Dove groaning]

25:49.983 --> 25:51.941
[Dwight grunting]

26:00.123 --> 26:03.518
Hey. I know
what you're doing.

26:03.649 --> 26:05.215
It's still there
right where I left it.

26:05.346 --> 26:07.043
No, I know why you want
to go fight those walkers alone.

26:07.174 --> 26:08.610
Why is that?

26:08.741 --> 26:11.308
Because you don't plan
on surviving, right?

26:11.439 --> 26:12.919
Maybe Dove was right.

26:13.049 --> 26:15.225
I mean, she's here
because of me. You all are.

26:15.356 --> 26:16.705
That is
defeatist bullshit.

26:16.836 --> 26:18.707
Yeah, it is
what it is, honey.

26:18.838 --> 26:21.057
Hey. D!

26:22.276 --> 26:23.625
D.
Yeah.

26:24.713 --> 26:26.062
It doesn't have to be.

26:26.193 --> 26:27.542
That guy that I tried
to help,

26:27.673 --> 26:30.284
he lost more
than just insulin.

26:30.414 --> 26:35.115
Okay? He had a wife.
He had a kid.

26:35.245 --> 26:38.118
Looks like he was
just about Finch's age.

26:38.248 --> 26:40.033
Alright?
I-I tried to help,

26:40.163 --> 26:42.470
and it just landed us right back
here in this hellhole, okay?

26:42.601 --> 26:44.341
And you can say
whatever you want to say,

26:44.472 --> 26:47.344
but this is not
a coincidence, okay?

26:47.475 --> 26:50.478
And it's not some defeatist
mentality or whatever.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.611
Alright.
Then tell me what it is.

26:55.788 --> 26:59.400
I drew that -- when
we were both living here.

26:59.530 --> 27:00.923
I put them
all over the place.

27:01.054 --> 27:02.795
Places where Negan
couldn't find them.

27:02.925 --> 27:04.274
Why?

27:04.405 --> 27:07.930
It was me and you.

27:08.061 --> 27:09.453
Forever.

27:09.584 --> 27:11.194
Kept me going.

27:12.587 --> 27:14.415
It made me feel
like we could

27:14.545 --> 27:17.461
turn something bad
into something good.

27:17.592 --> 27:19.725
D, it can.
No, we can't!

27:19.855 --> 27:21.422
Alright? Not with us!

27:21.552 --> 27:25.469
And I'm so tired of
making people suffer for it!

27:25.600 --> 27:27.907
Alright?!

27:28.037 --> 27:31.519
So you're just gonna
go kill yourself?

27:31.650 --> 27:34.522
I'm gonna clear
the walkers.

27:34.653 --> 27:38.569
And -- And maybe if I clear
them, maybe that'll save Dove.

27:38.700 --> 27:42.008
Maybe that'll honor Finch.
Isn't that what you said?

27:42.138 --> 27:43.749
You selfish asshole!

27:43.879 --> 27:48.710
♪♪

27:48.841 --> 27:51.017
Sherry!
You don't get to give up like this!

27:51.147 --> 27:52.714
[Pounding]

27:52.845 --> 27:56.022
Dwight:
Sherry! Sherry! Sherry!

27:56.152 --> 27:57.719
[Pounding]

28:00.896 --> 28:02.724
[Walkers growling]

28:02.855 --> 28:05.422
[Metal clanging]

28:05.553 --> 28:09.513
♪♪

28:09.644 --> 28:11.428
[Rattling]

28:16.695 --> 28:19.828
[Metal creaking]

28:19.959 --> 28:21.482
Why can't you
just do it now?

28:21.612 --> 28:23.397
We have to wait for
the building to be stable.

28:23.527 --> 28:27.096
And I need --
I need the extra hands.

28:27.227 --> 28:30.534
This is about your finger.
What happened on the train?

28:30.665 --> 28:32.536
You said so yourself!

28:32.667 --> 28:34.364
You need stay calm. Okay?

28:34.495 --> 28:36.018
If your heart rate spikes,
you could --

28:36.149 --> 28:37.890
No, no. What's the real reason,
Blue Jay?!

28:38.020 --> 28:40.109
It's not important.

28:40.240 --> 28:43.112
You're a nurse. Okay?

28:43.243 --> 28:46.594
A-And I've got a bullet in me,
a bullet you won't take out.

28:46.725 --> 28:47.987
We're going to take it out.

28:48.117 --> 28:49.466
Every minute you wait
is a minute I could die!

28:49.597 --> 28:50.990
You're not going to die!

28:51.120 --> 28:53.514
Tell me why.
Tell me why!

28:53.644 --> 28:57.257
Because what happened to them
isn't going to happen to you!

28:57.387 --> 29:00.303
Who is "them"?

29:00.434 --> 29:02.784
Finch.

29:02.915 --> 29:04.220
And Hannah.

29:04.351 --> 29:06.875
[Walkers growling]

29:07.006 --> 29:09.791
Rose. My daughter.

29:13.752 --> 29:15.710
[Metal clanging]

29:15.841 --> 29:17.103
You have a kid?

29:17.233 --> 29:18.669
Yeah.

29:20.367 --> 29:25.241
Hm. She would have been
about your age now.

29:25.372 --> 29:26.808
What happened to Rose?

29:30.594 --> 29:33.293
Uh, she had pneumonia.

29:33.423 --> 29:36.383
And, um, I went out
to look for medicine,

29:36.513 --> 29:39.778
and I came back and...

29:39.908 --> 29:43.172
just was too late.

29:46.175 --> 29:49.091
[Sobs]

29:49.222 --> 29:50.876
I couldn't save her.

29:51.006 --> 29:55.794
♪♪

29:55.924 --> 29:59.145
[Sobs] Just like
I couldn't save Finch.

29:59.275 --> 30:05.629
♪♪

30:05.760 --> 30:07.806
You know,
PADRE was right.

30:10.634 --> 30:12.941
You can't protect me.

30:13.072 --> 30:15.944
None of you
can protect me!

30:16.075 --> 30:17.685
We can.
No.

30:17.816 --> 30:19.252
That's what
we're going to do!

30:19.382 --> 30:21.645
No, you can't!

30:21.776 --> 30:24.213
It's exactly why
I wanted to get away.

30:24.344 --> 30:26.781
What are you
talking about?

30:26.912 --> 30:29.915
I didn't come here
for Red Kite.

30:30.045 --> 30:34.006
I came here to get as far away
from PADRE as I could.

30:34.136 --> 30:36.922
I was trying
to run away from you.

30:37.052 --> 30:39.402
But you said it was the only
home you'd ever known.

30:39.533 --> 30:40.751
<i>Was.</i>

30:42.492 --> 30:44.886
But that's gone now.

30:45.017 --> 30:48.934
Because people like you
are in charge now.

30:49.064 --> 30:52.067
People who will
just let us down,

30:52.198 --> 30:53.808
because that's what people

30:53.939 --> 30:56.767
who can't get over
their own shit do!

30:58.769 --> 31:00.597
[Metal banging]

31:03.731 --> 31:06.081
Dwight. Sherry.
What's happening?

31:07.430 --> 31:08.823
[Gunshot]

31:08.954 --> 31:10.999
<i>Dwight. Sherry.</i>
<i>Do you copy?</i>

31:11.130 --> 31:13.045
[Gunshot]

31:13.175 --> 31:14.742
I'm working on it.

31:14.873 --> 31:18.137
<i>Just you?</i>
<i>Where's Dwight?</i>

31:18.267 --> 31:20.008
I locked him
in his old room.

31:20.139 --> 31:22.402
What?!
Why would you do that?

31:22.532 --> 31:24.012
<i>PADRE needs him.</i>

31:24.143 --> 31:26.449
<i>Those kids will follow him </i>
<i>to the end of the Earth.</i>

31:26.580 --> 31:27.711
You know I'm right.

31:27.842 --> 31:30.540
<i>What about you?</i>
<i>We need you.</i>

31:30.671 --> 31:32.586
I can keep them
distracted.

31:32.716 --> 31:34.936
<i>You can't handle them</i>
<i>all on your own.</i>

31:35.067 --> 31:37.896
June, just do
what we came to do.

31:38.026 --> 31:40.855
<i>Help Dove...</i>
<i>and get Dwight back to PADRE.</i>

31:40.986 --> 31:42.335
Promise me, June.

31:42.465 --> 31:43.727
[Gunshot]

31:43.858 --> 31:45.425
[Walkers growling]

31:45.555 --> 31:46.992
[Fence rattling]

31:47.122 --> 31:48.428
[Sherry screams]

31:49.864 --> 31:51.213
[Pounding]

31:51.344 --> 31:52.388
Dwight: Sherry!

31:52.519 --> 31:54.173
[Grunts]

31:54.303 --> 31:57.045
Sherry!

31:57.176 --> 31:58.307
Sherry!

31:58.438 --> 31:59.961
[Walkers growling]

32:00.092 --> 32:01.441
[Sherry grunting]

32:01.571 --> 32:03.095
<i>Sherry, do you copy?</i>

32:03.225 --> 32:05.575
[Walkers growling]

32:05.706 --> 32:06.968
<i>Sherry?!</i>

32:07.099 --> 32:10.624
♪♪

32:10.754 --> 32:14.323
♪♪

32:14.454 --> 32:15.803
[Grunts]

32:15.934 --> 32:18.675
♪♪

32:18.806 --> 32:20.460
[Sherry gasps]

32:20.590 --> 32:22.027
[Walkers growling]

32:22.157 --> 32:26.770
♪♪

32:26.901 --> 32:31.514
♪♪

32:31.645 --> 32:33.473
<i>Sherry!</i>

32:33.603 --> 32:35.649
<i>Come in! Sherry!</i>

32:39.479 --> 32:40.828
[Dwight shouts]

32:40.959 --> 32:43.004
[Breathing heavily]

32:46.442 --> 32:48.183
[Walkers growling]

32:48.314 --> 32:55.712
♪♪

32:55.843 --> 33:03.372
♪♪

33:03.503 --> 33:04.808
[Inhales deeply]

33:04.939 --> 33:06.549
[Sobs]

33:06.680 --> 33:13.078
♪♪

33:13.208 --> 33:19.606
♪♪

33:19.736 --> 33:21.260
June: Sherry needs you.

33:21.390 --> 33:24.306
♪♪

33:24.437 --> 33:25.873
What?

33:26.004 --> 33:27.831
♪♪

33:27.962 --> 33:29.920
[Walkers growling]

33:30.051 --> 33:34.925
♪♪

33:35.056 --> 33:39.843
♪♪

33:39.974 --> 33:44.805
♪♪

33:44.935 --> 33:46.415
[Gasps]

33:49.027 --> 33:51.855
[Dove groaning]

33:51.986 --> 33:53.596
Dove?

33:55.642 --> 33:57.078
Dove, stop! No!

33:57.209 --> 33:58.732
Get away from me!

33:58.862 --> 34:02.605
Oh, my god.

34:02.736 --> 34:04.259
You tried to get
the bullet out.

34:04.390 --> 34:06.522
I'm trying.

34:06.653 --> 34:08.742
I'm going to.

34:08.872 --> 34:11.919
Dove, you'll die.
You -- You need help.

34:12.050 --> 34:14.487
[Crying] I'm not
gonna get it from them.

34:14.617 --> 34:16.750
And I'm not gonna
get it from you!

34:16.880 --> 34:24.192
♪♪

34:24.323 --> 34:25.541
Dove, no, no, no, no.

34:25.672 --> 34:28.283
Dove, no, no, no.
No, no. Stop. Dove.

34:32.766 --> 34:34.376
Dove.

34:34.507 --> 34:35.899
Dove?

34:36.030 --> 34:37.597
[Walkers growling]

34:37.727 --> 34:39.294
- How did you get out here?
- June let me out. Thank God.

34:39.425 --> 34:41.122
I had it covered.
You expect me to believe that?

34:41.253 --> 34:42.863
You don't even believe that
for yourself.

34:42.993 --> 34:44.473
- What are you talking about?
- You've been lying ever since

34:44.604 --> 34:45.953
you showed up here!

34:46.084 --> 34:47.346
I haven't lied
about anything.

34:47.476 --> 34:49.478
You said this was
about honoring Finch,

34:49.609 --> 34:52.090
t-that you wanted to keep me
alive to fight for PADRE,

34:52.220 --> 34:53.395
and that's bullshit!

34:53.526 --> 34:54.614
You're wrong, D.

34:54.744 --> 34:56.224
Am I? Am I?

34:56.355 --> 34:59.967
Or...did you just lock me up
because you were planning

35:00.098 --> 35:02.535
on doing the same thing
I was out here?

35:02.665 --> 35:04.885
You think
I wanted to die? I know you did!

35:05.015 --> 35:06.887
And I know you don't believe
in that crap

35:07.017 --> 35:09.455
about good coming from bad.
I-I do!

35:09.585 --> 35:11.892
No. You <i>want</i>to.
I do, too. But it can't.

35:12.022 --> 35:14.068
If that's true, D, I don't know
how to go on living!

35:14.199 --> 35:15.809
Well, me neither!

35:19.247 --> 35:21.423
June:
<i>Sherry? Dwight?</i>

35:21.554 --> 35:23.382
W-We're outside.

35:23.512 --> 35:25.079
We're just trying to keep
them away from the building.

35:25.210 --> 35:26.863
<i>We have another problem.</i>

35:26.994 --> 35:29.692
<i>Dove. S-She tried to take</i>
<i>the bullet out herself.</i>

35:29.823 --> 35:31.694
What?
Why would she do that?

35:31.825 --> 35:34.610
<i>She didn't believe</i>
<i>any of us could.</i>

35:34.741 --> 35:36.046
[Gunshots]

35:36.177 --> 35:42.009
♪♪

35:42.140 --> 35:44.142
Had a feeling
I'd find you here.

35:44.272 --> 35:45.404
Shit.

35:45.534 --> 35:50.887
♪♪

35:51.018 --> 35:56.502
♪♪

36:00.636 --> 36:06.294
[Walkers growling]

36:06.425 --> 36:07.861
[Rattling]

36:13.083 --> 36:14.998
[Footsteps approach]

36:15.129 --> 36:16.652
Our friends are here.

36:16.783 --> 36:18.437
I've locked the door,
but it won't hold much longer.

36:18.567 --> 36:20.308
Sherry:
Neither will the building.

36:20.439 --> 36:23.311
We have to get out and move her
somewhere safer for the surgery.

36:23.442 --> 36:25.226
We need to move now!

36:25.357 --> 36:35.105
♪♪

36:35.236 --> 36:37.064
[Metal clanging]

36:37.195 --> 36:40.502
♪♪

36:40.633 --> 36:42.504
[Walkers growling]

36:42.635 --> 36:48.597
♪♪

36:48.728 --> 36:54.777
♪♪

36:54.908 --> 36:57.867
Surrounded.
I got her. I got her.

36:57.998 --> 37:00.174
♪♪

37:00.305 --> 37:02.089
[Gunshot]

37:02.220 --> 37:04.047
[Man grunting]

37:06.093 --> 37:07.225
Sherry:
We got to get out of here.

37:07.355 --> 37:08.922
Dwight:
There's nowhere to go.

37:10.619 --> 37:11.838
[Grunts]

37:11.968 --> 37:14.101
[Walkers growling]

37:14.232 --> 37:21.935
♪♪

37:22.065 --> 37:29.812
♪♪

37:29.943 --> 37:37.733
♪♪

37:37.864 --> 37:39.039
Sherry! Look out!

37:39.169 --> 37:40.388
[Grunts]

37:40.519 --> 37:41.824
Sherry...

37:43.652 --> 37:44.958
June.

37:45.088 --> 37:46.612
[Walker growling]
No.

37:49.223 --> 37:50.616
[Growling stops]

37:52.357 --> 37:53.445
Sherry.

37:53.575 --> 37:55.751
[Walkers growling]

37:55.882 --> 38:00.190
♪♪

38:00.321 --> 38:02.062
...there.

38:02.192 --> 38:04.804
[Walker growling]

38:07.154 --> 38:10.244
Do you remember
what I told you?

38:10.375 --> 38:13.682
About giving my friend
satisfaction?

38:15.205 --> 38:17.686
[Laughing]

38:17.817 --> 38:20.820
I think I'm going to enjoy this
even more than him.

38:23.388 --> 38:24.780
[Grunts]

38:27.653 --> 38:29.481
[Marty screaming]

38:35.051 --> 38:36.705
There's nowhere to go.

38:40.840 --> 38:42.102
Inside.
The fire's out.

38:42.232 --> 38:44.409
- What?
- Get in here.

38:44.539 --> 38:46.672
Okay. Come on.
Come on. Here we go.

38:46.802 --> 38:50.328
♪♪

38:50.458 --> 38:52.068
[Walkers growling]

38:52.199 --> 38:57.900
♪♪

38:58.031 --> 39:00.338
[Crashing]

39:00.468 --> 39:02.078
[Walkers growling]

39:03.993 --> 39:06.082
[Metal clanging]

39:10.086 --> 39:11.958
[Groans]
What happened?

39:12.088 --> 39:13.960
Why -- Why are we
in here?

39:14.090 --> 39:17.833
The building's
collapsing.

39:17.964 --> 39:19.182
It still hurts.

39:19.313 --> 39:20.619
I'm so sorry, Dove.

39:20.749 --> 39:22.055
This was never
gonna work.

39:22.185 --> 39:23.970
No, no, no.
No. Don't give up.

39:24.100 --> 39:27.713
You can't help me.
You can't help us.

39:32.718 --> 39:34.284
M-Maybe we can.

39:34.415 --> 39:37.200
[Metal clanging]

39:37.331 --> 39:38.593
What are you
talking about?

39:38.724 --> 39:40.465
The furnace is stable.

39:40.595 --> 39:42.336
[Metal clanging]

39:42.467 --> 39:47.602
T-That'll protect us from
whatever's happening out there.

39:47.733 --> 39:50.344
We could do the surgery
in here.

39:50.475 --> 39:52.651
Hey.
You can do it, June.

39:52.781 --> 39:55.697
- I can't.
- Yes, you can.

39:55.828 --> 39:57.395
How do you know?

39:57.525 --> 39:59.222
[Metal clanging]

40:01.790 --> 40:04.880
Because Sherry is right.

40:05.011 --> 40:07.056
A-About what?

40:07.187 --> 40:10.233
You know,
maybe something good

40:10.364 --> 40:11.974
can come
from something bad,

40:12.105 --> 40:16.152
a-and maybe there's a reason
that we all wound up in here,

40:16.283 --> 40:18.677
and we just needed
each other to see it.

40:18.807 --> 40:24.291
♪♪

40:24.422 --> 40:27.381
I don't want
to hurt you.

40:27.512 --> 40:29.122
Then don't.

40:29.252 --> 40:32.299
You can do this, June.

40:32.430 --> 40:35.389
What happened to you...
what happened to all of us...

40:35.520 --> 40:38.958
it doesn't
have to happen again.

40:39.088 --> 40:41.613
And maybe we --

40:41.743 --> 40:43.963
Maybe we just needed
to work through the bad

40:44.093 --> 40:45.530
to get to the good.

40:45.660 --> 40:53.146
♪♪

40:53.276 --> 40:54.756
Do you trust me?

40:56.715 --> 40:58.630
Ask me after
you get the bullet out.

40:58.760 --> 41:00.370
Okay?

41:03.548 --> 41:05.027
Fair enough.

41:05.158 --> 41:13.645
♪♪

41:13.775 --> 41:15.864
[Walkers growling]

41:15.995 --> 41:21.000
♪♪

41:21.130 --> 41:26.309
♪♪

41:29.791 --> 41:39.845
[Walkers growling]

41:49.115 --> 41:51.509
[Walker growling]

41:51.639 --> 41:53.380
Holy shit.

41:55.817 --> 41:57.906
[Walkers growling]

42:01.954 --> 42:03.521
It's over.

42:05.000 --> 42:06.698
[Walkers growling]

42:14.053 --> 42:15.750
Dwight:
How's she doing?

42:18.492 --> 42:21.190
She's still resting.

42:21.321 --> 42:23.279
She's gonna be okay.

42:31.679 --> 42:32.898
It's a Finch.

42:33.028 --> 42:39.948
♪♪

42:40.079 --> 42:42.124
[Bird chirping]

42:42.255 --> 42:48.217
♪♪

42:48.348 --> 42:54.310
♪♪

42:54.441 --> 42:58.227
Should probably
hit the road.

42:58.358 --> 42:59.620
Dwight: Ah.

42:59.751 --> 43:02.318
How you doing, kid?

43:02.449 --> 43:05.583
Better now.
You coming with us?

43:11.676 --> 43:13.982
Yes. Yeah, I am.

43:15.636 --> 43:20.119
Yeah.
N-Never should have left.

43:20.249 --> 43:22.425
Maybe we can turn that place
into what it's supposed to be.

43:22.556 --> 43:24.253
You know?

43:24.384 --> 43:26.908
The way
that Finch wanted it.

43:27.039 --> 43:29.650
Yeah. I think we can.

43:29.781 --> 43:33.045
♪♪

43:33.175 --> 43:35.438
Oh, uh, June.

43:35.569 --> 43:37.789
I made something for you.

43:37.919 --> 43:41.749
♪♪

43:41.880 --> 43:43.272
Thank you.

43:45.144 --> 43:47.276
You know,
back at the train car,

43:47.407 --> 43:49.714
um, before it went
the way that it did,

43:49.844 --> 43:52.368
I asked you to be
a part of our family.

43:52.499 --> 43:55.720
♪♪

43:55.850 --> 43:57.896
I -- And I-I ran away.

43:58.026 --> 44:00.463
But I'm -- I'm here now.

44:02.727 --> 44:05.207
So that offer
still extends to you.

44:06.948 --> 44:10.604
A-And to you, as well.

44:10.735 --> 44:12.127
Thanks, Red Kite.

44:12.258 --> 44:14.477
No, you don't --

44:14.608 --> 44:17.045
We're family.
It's Dwight.

44:19.265 --> 44:20.875
It's Odessa.

44:23.399 --> 44:24.662
Odessa?

44:27.708 --> 44:29.231
I like it.

44:29.362 --> 44:32.452
♪♪

44:32.582 --> 44:35.150
Alright. We should go.
We got a lot of work to do.

44:35.281 --> 44:36.543
Yeah.

44:36.674 --> 44:42.070
♪♪

44:42.201 --> 44:47.641
♪♪

44:47.772 --> 44:49.861
[Engine starts]

44:49.991 --> 44:55.083
♪♪

44:55.214 --> 45:00.523
♪♪

45:05.659 --> 45:08.488
♪ <i>Count the drops in a stream</i>♪

45:08.618 --> 45:11.534
♪ <i>Run and catch the wind</i>♪

45:11.665 --> 45:14.886
♪ <i>Sail to Spain on a dream</i>♪

45:15.016 --> 45:17.149
♪ <i>Run and catch the wind</i>♪

45:17.279 --> 45:19.238
Troy:
<i>Have you found her yet?</i>

45:19.368 --> 45:23.024
Russell: <i>Nothing yet, Troy.</i>
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

45:23.155 --> 45:24.852
<i>Stop telling me</i>
<i>that you're sorry.</i>

45:24.983 --> 45:26.941
<i>Because there's nothing</i>
<i>to be sorry for.</i>

45:27.072 --> 45:30.075
<i>My daughter is alive.</i>
<i>And I will find her.</i>

45:30.205 --> 45:33.339
♪ <i>Traveling free</i>
<i>through the field</i>♪

45:33.469 --> 45:35.994
[Music shuts off]

45:36.124 --> 45:41.651
[Girl screaming]

45:41.782 --> 45:45.917
What is this place?!
Where am I?

45:46.047 --> 45:48.180
Where's my dad?!

45:48.310 --> 45:50.965
Let go of me!

45:51.096 --> 45:55.143
[Screaming]

45:55.274 --> 45:57.319
[Speaking German]

46:06.024 --> 46:09.244
It's okay.
I'm just gonna remove this.

46:16.861 --> 46:19.341
Who are you?

46:19.472 --> 46:21.430
What do you want
with me?

46:22.910 --> 46:25.565
My name is Victor.

46:25.695 --> 46:28.089
Good thing we found you
when we did.

46:28.220 --> 46:29.569
Why?

46:29.699 --> 46:33.268
I'm gonna help you.
You're gonna help me.

46:33.399 --> 46:35.488
Help you do what?

46:36.794 --> 46:38.839
Save PADRE.

46:38.970 --> 46:47.500
♪♪

46:52.287 --> 46:53.723
Madison:
The entire herd is stuck.

46:53.854 --> 46:54.942
Alicia was in the herd.

46:55.073 --> 46:56.857
Alicia.

46:58.598 --> 47:00.905
This isn't about me.
It's about her.

47:01.079 --> 47:01.993
It's about PADRE.

47:02.123 --> 47:03.559
♪♪

47:03.733 --> 47:05.779
Wait for me.

47:05.953 --> 47:08.434
What makes you think I'm gonna
make a deal with you?

47:08.608 --> 47:10.131
[Walkers growling]

47:10.262 --> 47:12.133
Ahh!

47:13.178 --> 47:15.136
This doesn't end well.

47:15.267 --> 47:17.008
For you.

47:17.225 --> 47:20.359
♪♪

47:21.360 --> 47:31.457
♪♪

47:33.938 --> 47:37.245
Goldberg: Dwight is in
a really dark place

47:37.376 --> 47:39.378
when we find him at
the beginning of this episode.

47:39.508 --> 47:41.423
[Thunder crashes]

47:41.554 --> 47:43.773
Amelio: We kind of talked about
the fact that I'm sort of

47:43.904 --> 47:48.866
at a point of, like, drifter,
wanderer who's hallucinating.

47:48.996 --> 47:50.955
We wanted him,
like, really far gone.

47:51.085 --> 47:53.740
He and Sherry, of course,
parted ways.

47:53.871 --> 47:58.353
They were both utterly broken
by the loss of their son.

47:58.484 --> 48:01.966
And Dwight
has this feeling that,

48:02.096 --> 48:04.229
as long as he and Sherry
are together,

48:04.359 --> 48:07.275
they're never gonna be able to
escape the pain from their past.

48:07.406 --> 48:08.755
It's just gonna
keep haunting him.

48:08.886 --> 48:10.975
He wants to die.

48:11.105 --> 48:14.108
♪♪

48:14.239 --> 48:16.067
[Vehicle door opens]

48:17.590 --> 48:19.418
D?

48:19.548 --> 48:21.028
What are you
doing here?

48:21.159 --> 48:23.291
We came here
to find you.

48:25.076 --> 48:28.601
Elfman: There's this sort of
mutual exchange of,

48:28.731 --> 48:31.430
"We all need each other
to get through our own trauma.

48:31.560 --> 48:34.085
We all mutually experienced
the pain of PADRE.

48:34.215 --> 48:36.261
And we have all lost a child."

48:36.391 --> 48:38.567
Through all of this trauma,
it's brought us back

48:38.698 --> 48:42.832
to Dwight and Sherry's original
trauma of them as a couple.

48:42.963 --> 48:47.098
We have some top-notch medical
supplies back at our place.

48:47.228 --> 48:49.839
Of course, you know that.
You were there.

48:49.970 --> 48:53.365
Where?

48:53.495 --> 48:55.149
Sanctuary.

48:57.412 --> 48:59.066
Evangelista: We're actually
in front of

48:59.197 --> 49:01.721
this pretty incredible set
that they built

49:01.851 --> 49:04.463
replicating the Sanctuary,
which was --

49:04.593 --> 49:06.160
They built it
in, like, a week.

49:06.291 --> 49:07.335
Did they?Yeah.

49:07.466 --> 49:10.077
2, 1...

49:10.208 --> 49:13.646
Goldberg:
Re-creating the Sanctuary

49:13.776 --> 49:17.955
was one of the tallest orders
we've ever done on the show.

49:18.085 --> 49:20.609
Every department needing to be
on the top of their game

49:20.740 --> 49:24.439
to take this iconic location
from "The Walking Dead"

49:24.570 --> 49:27.442
and re-create it on a scale
that we could for this episode.

49:27.573 --> 49:29.879
It was incredibly exciting
to see

49:30.010 --> 49:31.969
how they were able
to pull that off.

49:32.099 --> 49:33.796
Amelio: It's really cool.
They did a really good job.

49:33.927 --> 49:36.582
It's different because it's
dilapidated and broken down.

49:36.712 --> 49:38.410
Evangelista:
It was so surreal to see

49:38.540 --> 49:40.716
the Sanctuary set
for the first time.

49:40.847 --> 49:44.024
I remember it so vividly,
so it really helps take us back

49:44.155 --> 49:47.288
and helps show just the
culmination for these characters

49:47.419 --> 49:49.812
and where they are now
and having this really

49:49.943 --> 49:52.554
cathartic experience here.

49:55.035 --> 50:00.388
Elfman:
You have an episode with, like, huge practical stunts

50:00.519 --> 50:03.000
and things falling
from the ceiling

50:03.130 --> 50:05.219
and around the walkers
and us running through.

50:05.350 --> 50:06.481
It felt so real.

50:06.612 --> 50:07.917
Look out!

50:08.048 --> 50:09.702
Ohh!
Sherry.

50:12.183 --> 50:14.141
Chambliss: The thing that
offered them salvation,

50:14.272 --> 50:17.536
the thing that saved
Dwight, Sherry, Dove, and June

50:17.666 --> 50:19.494
when the Sanctuary
came collapsing down

50:19.625 --> 50:22.280
was, in fact, the furnace,
kind of this thing

50:22.410 --> 50:24.760
that is a symbol
of everything they lost,

50:24.891 --> 50:26.719
where Dwight's face was burned,

50:26.849 --> 50:29.461
where their lives
were torn apart.

50:29.591 --> 50:32.377
Dwight: Maybe there's a reason
that we all wound up in here

50:32.507 --> 50:34.988
and we just needed
each other to see it.

50:35.119 --> 50:38.383
And they realize
that maybe turning to trauma

50:38.513 --> 50:40.820
is the way you have
to push through it

50:40.950 --> 50:43.214
so that they can actually
start to heal together

50:43.344 --> 50:46.521
and start to find a way
to remember their son.

50:46.652 --> 50:49.220
And that, ultimately to them,
I think, is a sign

50:49.350 --> 50:52.440
that maybe they need to look
at kind of the wreckage

50:52.571 --> 50:55.443
that they see their life is
and start to rebuild that.

50:55.574 --> 50:58.316
Let go of me!

50:58.446 --> 51:01.406
Chambliss: After we've seen
Strand and his new family

51:01.536 --> 51:04.931
and seeing that he genuinely has
made a real effort to change,

51:05.062 --> 51:07.020
I think the last thing
we're expecting

51:07.151 --> 51:09.414
was he's got
this 8-year-old girl

51:09.544 --> 51:11.546
who is very scared

51:11.677 --> 51:15.637
locked in a jail cell
underground at PADRE.

51:15.768 --> 51:18.118
Is he doing this ultimately
for the greater good,

51:18.249 --> 51:20.251
or is he doing this once again

51:20.381 --> 51:22.427
because it's what's best
for Victor Strand?

51:22.557 --> 51:24.820
Those are kind of some questions
that we're gonna get answers for

51:24.951 --> 51:27.040
in the next couple of episodes.

51:27.171 --> 51:30.217
I'm gonna help you.
You're gonna help me.

51:30.348 --> 51:32.567
Help you do what?

51:34.091 --> 51:36.441
Save PADRE.

51:36.571 --> 51:42.577
♪♪

51:45.493 --> 51:54.850
♪♪

51:54.981 --> 52:04.338
♪♪

52:04.469 --> 52:14.000
♪♪
